title: Oman Cricket A division matches: Victories for Enhance Eagles, Renaissance Teams
text:
Oman Cricket A division matches: Victories for Enhance Eagles, Renaissance Teams Wasim Ali of Enhance Eagles October 12, 2015 
Enhance Eagles hammered Hasan Juma Backer (HJB) by six wickets and Renaissance coasted to a four-wicket win against Indian Social Club (ISC) in their respective Oman Cricket (OC) A division matches at Al Amerat over the weekend. 
Upon winning the toss and batting first, HJB made 172 in 28.2 overs with Asif Ilyas (37) and Waleed Younus (31) top-scoring. Wasim Ali claimed five for 25. In reply, Eagles completed a bonus-point victory by chasing the score down in 19 overs. Guru Prasanna hit 59. 
Aadil Mohammed of Fairtrade 
The other match saw ISC bowled out for 148 in 26.5 overs. Tauseef Ahmed picked four wickets. Chasing a modest target, Mohammed Yaqoob top-scored with 44 to lead Renaissance to victory for the loss of six wickets in 24.1 overs. 
Brief scores: HJB 172 in 28.2 overs (Ilyas 37, Younus 31; Ali 5-25, Khalid Latif 3-20 lost to Enhance Eagles 174-4 in 19 overs (Prasanna 59, Ivan Manjila 38; Ali Hassan 2-37). 
ISC 148 in 26.5 overs (Ansar Ansari 26; Ahmed 4-22) lost to Renaissance 149-6 in 24.1 overs (Yaqoob 44; Hemil Ganatra 3-21). 
Other results: B division: OCT Seeb 127-9 in 20 overs (Issa Rahim 35; Ranjith Nair 2-15) lost to Fairtrade 131-2 in 14.2 overs (Aadil Mohammed 75 n.o). 
C division: Ernst & Young 193-4 in 20 overs (Nayaz Mohammed 59 n.o, Vikram Verma 45) beat Larsen & Toubro 165 in 19.2 overs (Altaf P K 61; Saud Haroon 2-21). 
D division: Landscape 165-6 in 20 overs (Prasad Peruli 47, Amrit Singh 40; Mohd Hanif 3-21) beat OCT Al Hail A 117-8 in 20 overs (Haroon al Balushi 46; Jamsheer 2-13, Shafiq 2-13). 
Mott MacDonald 138-9 in 20 overs (Samir More 28; Imran Ali 3-21) lost to Future Oilfield 141-2 in 14 overs (Mohammed Amjad 49, Imran Ali 48 n.o). Similar content
